Description : Head : Scales ranging from light brownish-grey and brownish-grey to brown. Antenna ca. 0.7–0.8x forewing length; dense, short, piliform cilia surround male flagellomere; female with less dense, piliform cilia on ventral side of flagellomere. Labial palpus mottled light brownish-grey and brownish-grey or light brown and brown; third segment ca. 0.2–0.4x length of second. Thorax : light brownish-grey to brown. Forewing length 9–16 mm ; ground color mottled very light brownish-grey to brownish-grey, or mostly brown; discal area often with several small blackish spots in cell and curving, poorly defined whitish band through terminal area; evenly spaced spots on distal half of costa and along termen at vein endings usually also present; however, these spots and line sometimes quite faint in brown individuals and occasionally absent altogether. Note: a rare form also has been collected, which has much lighter coloration (fig. 2 A). Hindwing: brownish-grey or brown, sometimes darker than forewing; fringe brownish-grey or brown. Abdomen : Dark brown to light brown. Male genitalia (
Fig. 72
) with apex of uncus deeply cleft; sacculus long and tapering to a sharp, free tip. Female genitalia typical for genus; signum long.
